Sentencas: Fe-Ni alloy is electrodeposited on ferritic stainless steel for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) interconnects application.
Titulo: Evaluation of electrodeposited Fe-Ni alloy on ferritic stainless steel solid oxide fuel cell interconnect

Sentencas: The oxidation behavior of Fe-Ni alloy coated steel has been investigated at 800 degrees C in air corresponding to the cathode environment of SOFC.
Titulo: Evaluation of electrodeposited Fe-Ni alloy on ferritic stainless steel solid oxide fuel cell interconnect

Sentencas: It is found that the oxidation rate of the Fe-Ni alloy coated steel becomes similar to that of the uncoated steel after the first week thermal exposure, although the mass gain of the coated steel is higher than that of the uncoated steel.
Titulo: Evaluation of electrodeposited Fe-Ni alloy on ferritic stainless steel solid oxide fuel cell interconnect

Sentencas: Oxide scale formed on the uncoated steel mainly consists of Cr2O3 with (Mn,Cr)(3)O-4 spinel.
Titulo: Evaluation of electrodeposited Fe-Ni alloy on ferritic stainless steel solid oxide fuel cell interconnect
Evaluation of electrodeposited Fe-Ni alloy on ferritic stainless steel solid oxide fuel cell interconnect

Sentencas: a double-layer oxide structure with a Cr-free outer layer of Fe2O3/NiFe2O4 and an inner layer of Cr2O3 is developed on the Fe-Ni alloy coated steel.
Titulo: Evaluation of electrodeposited Fe-Ni alloy on ferritic stainless steel solid oxide fuel cell interconnect

Sentencas: The scale area specific resistance (ASR) for the Fe-Ni alloy coated steel is lower than that of the scale for the uncoated steel.
Titulo: Evaluation of electrodeposited Fe-Ni alloy on ferritic stainless steel solid oxide fuel cell interconnect
